		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mappa-mercia.org/?p=1076#comment-318</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[I don&#039;t think I would have kept contributing if not for the resources on the wiki; taginfo is useful when you&#039;re not sure what the appropriate tag/word/category might be, but the wiki usually seems the best place for finding what those tags are supposed to represent. The various photos uploaded as examples for various tags (like the surface page) have been particularly useful.

But if you live outside one of the more popular OSM countries, you quickly learn to take things with a grain of salt - which is pretty much your point #4. And then there&#039;s all the &#039;proposed features&#039; and contradictory &#039;V2.0&#039; proposals and so on. I tend to treat it more like &quot;this is how things are usually done in Europe&quot;, not &quot;this is how things MUST be done everywhere&quot;.

While there are specific pages for my country they&#039;re pretty vague on the few details mentioned. I probably could update a few bits myself but I&#039;m wary of this overall situation - I don&#039;t want others to think my personal preferences are the rule!]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I don&#8217;t think I would have kept contributing if not for the resources on the wiki; taginfo is useful when you&#8217;re not sure what the appropriate tag/word/category might be, but the wiki usually seems the best place for finding what those tags are supposed to represent. The various photos uploaded as examples for various tags (like the surface page) have been particularly useful.</p>
<p>But if you live outside one of the more popular OSM countries, you quickly learn to take things with a grain of salt &#8211; which is pretty much your point #4. And then there&#8217;s all the &#8216;proposed features&#8217; and contradictory &#8216;V2.0&#8217; proposals and so on. I tend to treat it more like &#8220;this is how things are usually done in Europe&#8221;, not &#8220;this is how things MUST be done everywhere&#8221;.</p>
<p>While there are specific pages for my country they&#8217;re pretty vague on the few details mentioned. I probably could update a few bits myself but I&#8217;m wary of this overall situation &#8211; I don&#8217;t want others to think my personal preferences are the rule!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
