					<description><![CDATA[Good post, and I agree with all your points. To me the wiki is important as it forms a major part of our documentation but I would love to see some improvement in the way that articles are written. Some are simply way too long for what should be a very basic concept, whilst others suffer from the so-called &quot;wiki-fiddling&quot; where someone changes something without taking time to consider impacts on a global community.

Point 6 above is particularly important.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Good post, and I agree with all your points. To me the wiki is important as it forms a major part of our documentation but I would love to see some improvement in the way that articles are written. Some are simply way too long for what should be a very basic concept, whilst others suffer from the so-called &#8220;wiki-fiddling&#8221; where someone changes something without taking time to consider impacts on a global community.</p>
<p>Point 6 above is particularly important.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
